results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of embeddings on the sphere of 2-connected planar graphs with n nodes and k faces up to orientation preserving isomorphisms, n >= 3, k=2..2*n-4.
comment: The number of edges is n+k-2.
Terms of this sequence can be computed using the tool "plantri". The expanded reference gives rows 3..15 of this table.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 3..171 (rows 3..15)
Gunnar Brinkmann and Brendan McKay, Fast generation of planar graphs (expanded edition), Tables 23-26.
